Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{0.5%tsp} for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

When boiling, add the potatoes and cook until tender, about ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @?oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and sprinkle over the
@plain flour{8%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir together to coat the
chicken.

Cook until golden on the outside, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

While the chicken cooks, trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the
@leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice. Trim the @green beans{80%g} then
chop into thirds.

Once the chicken is browned, add the leek and @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the
pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook until the mushrooms have
browned and the leek softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Once the veggies are soft, add in the @red wine stock paste{28%g} and
@water{150%ml}. Add the green beans, bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve
stock pot.

Simmer until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of water if
it's a bit thick.

Put your potatoes back in the pan and add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash
of @?milk{} if you have it.

Grate in the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} and mash with a #potato masher{}
until smooth.

Serve in #bowls{} with the chicken stew on top. Enjoy!